race.comment: ONE HARD LADY (5) classy mare with a smart winning record. Undefeated at this track and should prove too sharp for these after knocking up late with a gritty second over 955m at Moonee Valley in BM74 class. No excuses from the draw and McDougall sticks. STARLIGHT GIRL (11) turned things around quickly at her third run back when a narrow second in fast time over 1000m at Canberra. A repeat effort can see her figuring in the minor money. HULM (4) is a distance specialist who was a total forgive when drawing out for a plodding twelfth over 955m at Moonee Valley. Blinkers go on for the first time and shapes as the value play. MR MOPPETT (2) has a sound record at this course and distance and will relish the weight drop today. Adept in all conditions and stays in the mix.
